<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the deceased has been positively identified as former Colonel Mohlabi Lazarus Tlomatsana who retired from the South African Police Service in 2007 at the age of 60.He was attached to the National Corporate Communication and Liaison in Pretoria at the time of his retirement.He said the gruesome discovery was made by the passerby on Saturday morning and  the police were alerted and reacted swiftly.Theojapelo said the victim appeared to have been tied inside the vehicle when it was set alight.The police have since launched a manhunt for the assailants and nobody was arrested so far. The motive for the incident is unknown at this stage and investigations are continuing."We are still making an appeal to anyone with information to contact Captain Richard Boshomane at 0798945501 or Captain Matsobane Chuene at 0824143345,"said MojapeloMeanwhile, the body of a person who was also found burned beyond recognition inside a burnt out Toyota double cap next to Christina village, has not yet been identified. The vehicle belonged to Veronica Mapula Mahanyele who went missing . Her body was found dumped in the bushes next to Newlands village at ga-Mashashane.Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspects involved in this incident and the positive identification of the deceased is requested to contact Captain Richard Boshomane on 079945501 or Warrant officer Galane on 0823008135.